    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCurrently, there is no easy way to detect when an extmark gets deleted.\r\nThis would be useful for two reasons: to sync an extmark_id to a data table with existing extmarks and so that UIs can detect when an extramark they watch gets deleted.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nA field called on_delete gets added to extmarks which gets called when the extmark gets deleted.",
    "closed_at": "2024-01-06T22:19:54Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Extmarks are owned by a specific plugin, and so far they are not designed to act as a generic API for other plugins to read from. They are sort of lower level than that.\n\nI think if you need to know when an extmark is removed you really should be asking when a plugin is removing them. E.g. in Gitsigns a user autocmd is triggered when hunks change.\n\nCan you at least provide some real world use cases?",
